The paper deals with iterative decoding of low-density parity-check codes over the Binary Symmetric channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method involves designing update functions based on knowledge of potentially harmful subgraphs, which could fall under the category of network information theory (cs.NI) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the complexity of the proposed method, which could be relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper compares the performance of the proposed method to the Belief propagation decoder, which is a common algorithm in coding theory (cs.CC).
